The paper presents an algorithm for learning Bayesian network structures, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The algorithm is based on the minimum description length (MDL) principle, which is a statistical method for model selection and compression (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the time complexity of the algorithm, which is a common concern in information theory and computer science (cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the algorithm for studying the adequacy of the MDL principle, which is a topic in information theory and statistical inference (cs.SI).
